caveman:
React re-renders child when parent renders — default behavior. Child gets new render call even if props unchanged.

Common causes + fixes:

**1. No memoization**
```jsx
// Wrap with React.memo to skip re-render when props same
const Child = React.memo(function Child({ name }) {
  return <div>{name}</div>;
});
```

**2. Inline objects/arrays/functions as props**
```jsx
// ❌ New reference every render → memo useless
<Child style={{ color: 'red' }} onClick={() => doThing()} />

// ✅ Stabilize references
const style = useMemo(() => ({ color: 'red' }), []);
const onClick = useCallback(() => doThing(), []);
<Child style={style} onClick={onClick} />
```

**3. Context changes**
Any context value change re-renders all consumers. Split contexts or memoize value:
```jsx
const value = useMemo(() => ({ user, theme }), [user, theme]);
<MyContext.Provider value={value}>
```

**4. Key changes**
If parent assigns new `key` to child, React unmounts + remounts (not just re-render).

**Debug tool:** React DevTools Profiler → "Why did this render?" Shows which props/state/hooks changed.

**Rule of thumb:** Don't memo everything preemptively. Measure first. `React.memo` + `useCallback`/`useMemo` add complexity — only worth it when re-renders cause visible perf issues.

